H0.text: Individuals are the number counted in population size in a population.

H1.text: Humans are the number counted in the population size of a population.

H2.text: Subdivisions are the number that constitutes the population size in a population.

H3.text: Proteins are the number that makes up the population size in a population.

A4.text: a population can be described by what individuals constitute the population, its size, a geographical area it occupies, and the time within which the population is examined

A5.text: In ecology, a population is a group of organisms of the same species which inhabit the same geographical area and are capable of interbreeding
